meta {
  name: chat — COMHRÁ (expected to fail)
  type: http
  seq: 3
}

post {
  url: {{chatBase}}/api/s2s
  body: json
  auth: none
}

headers {
  Origin: {{origin}}
  Referer: {{chatReferer}}
  User-Agent: {{userAgent}}
  Accept: */*
  Content-Type: application/json
}

body:json {
  {
    "messages": [
      { "role": "assistant", "content": "Dia dhuit! Is mise do chomhairleoir Gaeilge. Conas is féidir liom cabhrú leat inniu?" },
      { "role": "user", "content": "hello" }
    ]
  }
}

docs {
  COMHRÁ (Irish chat) endpoint. **This request is expected to fail (401/403)**
  because the endpoint is protected by Google's Web App Attestation. The token
  is bound to a real browser session on abair.ie and cannot be reproduced from
  Bruno or curl.

  Documented here for completeness. Response shape when it works (browser only):
    { "text": "Dia dhuit! Conas atá cúrsaí leat?" }

  For a working Irish chat loop server-side: use transcribe.bru for STT, your
  own LLM for the reply, and synthesise.bru for TTS. See ../SKILL.md § Chat.
}
